The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, July 02, 2004 				 Centurion Bank Q1 net at Rs 3 crore
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 																								Mumbai, July 1: With a new management at the helm and a strong focus on retail banking, Centurion Bank has posted a first-quarter profit of Rs 3.15 crore compared with Rs 0.40 crore in the same period in 2003-04.																								Total income was down to Rs 91.68 crore from Rs 93.63 crore in the corresponding previous quarter.																								In 2003-04, the banks losses had increased to Rs 105.14 crore from Rs 25.36 crore in the previous year.																								As part of a clean-up exercise, the bank has made significant provisioning for bad assets. Provisioning cover is now at over 69 per cent of gross non-performing assets (NPAs).																								The banks net NPA level has been trimmed to 4.3 per cent of net advances compared with 7.5 per cent in the previous year. The bank continued its focus on the retail segment with retail assets and deposits each comprising over 80 per cent of the total.																								Centurion Bank plans to double its branch network in the next three years.
